 an art teacher tell me once (actualey allot and it annoyed the f*dg out of me) that you can NOT draw chainmail. you can draw lines and shapes that can fool the eye into thinking it's chain mail... what i think he meant by this is to look at the basic shape of the object you are trying to draw. chainmail is made of rings. hundreds of tiny rings linked togather. that's the basic shape. now comes the tricky part. drawing it realisticly. BTW i do LOVE the pic so far. ^_^ <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/usakumaryuichi.showPublicProfile?language=EN>sakuma ryuichi</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(12/29/01 4:53:59 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3994.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.geocities.com/rufi013/rufioownz.txt height=100 width=100></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: How do you draw chain mail?</span><hr size=1> hey, not bad! i don't know how to draw chainmail, i suppose there might be a comic tone somewhere that would allow you to make something look like chainmail, or shade it roughly, and it might fool appearances. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  anyway, there isn't very much to crit on your picture, as far as i can tell it's pretty good. however the lighter pencil shading, doesnt really fit in with the style. its a good style, though.  <p><a href="http://kumagorou.cjb.net"><img src="http://www.geocities.com/rufi013/link-1.txt" border="0"></a> <a href="http://rufio.pitas.com"><img src="http://www.geocities.com/rufi013/link.txt" border="0"></a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#aaaaaa><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.co