rd.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><br>or u can do it the hard good lookin' way.<br><br>i got a refference pic, don't know if its good material for u,<br><br>its a good closeup on a chain mail.. here's the link if it works;<br><br><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://hem.passagen.se/dudemaffia/picz/orcref.jpg">hem.passagen.se/dudemaffi...orcref.jpg</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--><br><br>hope u enjoy it! and hope the link works, it explains quite good how a chain mail is built... <p><B>Self improvement is masturbation. Maybe self destruction is the answer<br>- Tyler Durden</B></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#aaaaaa><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/ukaminosenshi.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kami no Senshi</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(12/29/01 8:28:09 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3994.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: How do you draw chain mail?</span><hr size=1> actually, ring mail is a lot of tiny rings, chain mail has links of chain. (really the only difference is in the strength of it and where you wear it).  I dont think your art teacher should be able to tell you what you can't draw, cause you can do it and make it look good,with a lot of time put into it. Also, knowing how it is made helps. <p><B> <I> I WISH i was Pat's Signature </B> </I> </p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/uclass666.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Class666</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(12/30/01 4:13:32 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3994.topic&ind